From a study table to a silver studio ✨
This is the story of how Simply Silver by Neha began — not in a fancy office or with a big plan, but with a quiet calling, a few boxes, and a lot of heart.

I didn’t love what I studied. But I loved making jewelry.
I worked, paused, restarted… took courses, built a small community, and one day, turned a garage into my dream studio.

Instagram was confusing, but kindness and connection made it all worth it.
And today, thanks to you, my little silver dream continues to grow.

🩶 Swipe through to see how it all unfolded…
📲 If you’d like to be part of the WhatsApp community where it all began — message me!
Love ❤️ & Gratitude

latestPosts.caption:
“Think vintage silver is just old and pretty? There’s a lot more behind that tarnished charm…”

What makes vintage silver special isn’t just its metal content, but the craftsmanship, natural tarnish (or patina), and the cultural context it carries. Each piece reflects the silversmith’s skill and the design sensibilities of its time, making it not just jewelry—but a piece of wearable history.

Vintage silver has so much character—and we’re all about it. As a brand, we cherish the charm of older pieces: real silver, rich stories, and timeless designs that never go out of style.

Yes! Most vintage silver pieces are made with real silver, often around 80% purity (also known as 800 silver). This was a common standard in many parts of the world before sterling (92.5%) became the norm.

The slightly lower purity gives vintage silver a distinct look and feel—a bit more muted in shine, but rich in character. It ages beautifully, developing a soft patina over time that adds to its antique charm and story.

Vintage silver pieces are timeless treasures—crafted in real silver, rich in history, and full of character.
